## 🧪 WakeStake - Comprehensive Test Review

---

## 1. Critical Test Cases (5)

### TC-001: Alarm Fires with Active Stake
```swift
func test_alarm_whenStakeActive_shouldTriggerChallengeAndBlockDismiss() {
    // Given: Alarm set for 6:00 AM with $5 stake
    // When: Clock hits 6:00 AM (even in background/killed state)
    // Then: 
    //   - Push notification fires with critical alert
    //   - Challenge screen appears (cannot swipe dismiss)
    //   - Snooze deducts from stake ($0.50)
    //   - Timer starts for challenge completion
}
```
**Risk:** User loses money if alarm doesn't fire → lawsuit territory.

---

### TC-002: Proof-of-Wake Challenge Verification
```swift
func test_proofOfWake_whenPhotoSubmitted_shouldValidateAndUnlockWallet() {
    // Given: User completes "Scan QR in kitchen" challenge
    // When: Photo submitted with correct QR code
    // Then:
    //   - Challenge marked complete
    //   - Stake returned to wallet
    //   - Streak counter incremented
    //   - Analytics event: "challenge_completed"
}
```
**Risk:** False negatives = angry users. False positives = system abuse.

---

### TC-003: RevenueCat Subscription State Sync
```swift
func test_subscription_whenPurchased_shouldUnlockPremiumFeatures() {
    // Given: Free user with 1 alarm limit
    // When: User purchases "WakeStake Pro" via RevenueCat
    // Then:
    //   - Unlimited alarms unlocked
    //   - Premium challenges available
    //   - Subscription status persists after reinstall
    //   - Restore purchases works on new device
}
```
**Risk:** User pays but doesn't get features = refund + bad review.

---

### TC-004: Escalating Stakes Calculation
```swift
func test_escalatingStakes_whenSnoozedMultipleTimes_shouldDeductCorrectly() {
    // Given: $10 stake, escalation: $1 → $2 → $4 per snooze
    // When: User snoozes 3 times then completes challenge
    // Then:
    //   - Total deducted: $7 (1+2+4)
    //   - Remaining returned: $3
    //   - Wallet balance accurate
    //   - Transaction history shows all deductions
}
```
**Risk:** Math errors with real money = trust destroyed.

---

### TC-005: Streak Cashback Reward
```swift
func test_streakCashback_when7DayStreakCompleted_shouldCreditWallet() {
    // Given: User has 6-day streak, completes day 7
    // When: Challenge completed on day 7
    // Then:
    //   - Cashback bonus added (e.g., 10% of week's stakes)
    //   - Celebration UI shown
    //   - Push notification: "🎉 7-day streak! $X earned"
    //   - Stats screen updated
}
```
**Risk:** Missing rewards = users feel cheated.

---

## 2. Edge Cases (3)

### EC-001: Alarm During Do Not Disturb / Focus Mode
```swift
func test_alarm_whenDNDEnabled_shouldStillFireAsCriticalAlert() {
    // Given: iOS Focus Mode active, alarm with stake set
    // When: Alarm time reached
    // Then:
    //   - Critical alert bypasses DND (requires entitlement)
    //   - Sound plays at full volume
    //   - If critical alert not permitted → show setup guide
}
```
**Why:** Users will blame app, not their settings.

---

### EC-002: Challenge Timeout with Network Failure
```swift
func test_challenge_whenNetworkLostDuringSubmission_shouldRetryAndNotPenalize() {
    // Given: User completes challenge, hits submit
    // When: Network drops during upload
    // Then:
    //   - Local proof cached
    //   - Retry with exponential backoff
    //   - Challenge timer paused during retry
    //   - User NOT penalized for network issues
    //   - Offline indicator shown
}
```
**Why:** Losing stake due to WiFi = rage uninstall.

---

### EC-003: Timezone Change (Travel Scenario)
```swift
func test_alarm_whenTimezoneChanges_shouldAdjustCorrectly() {
    // Given: Alarm set for 7:00 AM in NYC (EST)
    // When: User flies to LA (PST) 
    // Then:
    //   - Option: "Keep 7 AM local" vs "Keep original time"
    //   - Clear UI showing adjusted time
    //   - Stakes still valid
    //   - Widget updates correctly
}
```
**Why:** Business travelers are prime users for this app.

---

## 3. Accessibility Checklist

| Category | Requirement | Test |
|----------|-------------|------|
| **VoiceOver** | Challenge instructions read aloud | Can blind user understand what to do? |
| **VoiceOver** | Wallet balance announced | "Your balance is $25.00" not "25 00" |
| **Dynamic Type** | All text scales to XXXL | No truncation on Set Alarm screen |
| **Color Contrast** | Dark mode meets 4.5:1 | Stake amount visible on dark background |
| **Color Independence** | Success/failure not color-only | Use ✅/❌ icons, not just green/red |
| **Haptics** | Alarm includes vibration pattern | Deaf users can wake up |
| **Reduce Motion** | Celebration animations respect setting | No confetti if reduced motion on |
| **Switch Control** | All buttons reachable | Challenge can be completed via switch |

### Quick Audit Command:
```bash
# Run Accessibility Audit
python3 /Users/kamil/clawd/skills/xcode-build/scripts/xcode.py test \
  -p WakeStake.xcodeproj -s WakeStakeUITests \
  -d "platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 15" \
  --only "WakeStakeUITests/AccessibilityTests"
```

---

## 4. Performance Concerns

| Area | Concern | Metric Target | Test Approach |
|------|---------|---------------|---------------|
| **Alarm Reliability** | Background execution limits | 100% fire rate | Test with app killed, low battery, low power mode |
| **Widget Updates** | Timeline refresh budget | Update within 15 min | Monitor `WidgetKit` timeline reloads |
| **Camera Challenge** | Frame processing speed | < 100ms per frame | Profile with Instruments → Time Profiler |
| **Firebase Sync** | Offline-first wallet | Sync < 3s on reconnect | Airplane mode → WiFi toggle test |
| **Cold Launch** | Time to interactive | < 2 seconds | `MetricKit` / `os_signpost` measurement |
| **Battery** | Background processing drain | < 5% overnight | 8-hour background test with alarm set |
| **Memory** | Challenge screen leaks | No growth over 10 cycles | Instruments → Leaks + Allocations |

### Instruments Profile:
```bash
# Battery drain test
xcrun simctl spawn booted log stream --predicate 'subsystem == "com.wakestake.app"' > wake_log.txt

# Memory leaks
leaks --atExit -- /path/to/WakeStake.app
```

---

## 🚨 Highest Risk Areas

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  MONEY FLOW: Stake → Challenge → Wallet → Cashback     │
│  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────     │
│  Every transaction MUST be:                             │
│  • Idempotent (retry-safe)                             │
│  • Auditable (full transaction log)                    │
│  • Reversible (support can refund)                     │
│  • Tested with: $0, $0.01, $999.99, negative values    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

